1
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,500
[TESSAI] No!

2
00:00:28,583 --> 00:00:29,541
[GOROBEI] Get down!

3
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:34,166
Katsushiro! No!

4
00:00:34,250 --> 00:00:35,875
Young Master...!
Do you have any idea

5
00:00:35,958 --> 00:00:38,166
what would happen if you
hit one of the Guardians?!

6
00:00:38,250 --> 00:00:40,500
You're frustrated as
anyone would be...

7
00:00:40,583 --> 00:00:43,666
And that is enough.

8
00:00:43,750 --> 00:00:47,791
These two are grateful
for your sacrifice.

9
00:00:47,875 --> 00:00:49,541
And they should be.

10
00:00:50,916 --> 00:00:53,291
You are the fifth samurai.

11
00:00:54,833 --> 00:00:55,875
Sensei!

12
00:00:55,958 --> 00:00:57,291
Well, what are you waiting for?!

13
00:00:57,375 --> 00:01:00,625
Go kill them!
That's what we hired you for!

14
00:01:00,708 --> 00:01:02,958
[RIKICHI GRUNTS]

15
00:01:03,041 --> 00:01:05,750
Your death won't be
worth anything here.

16
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:08,666
[RIKICHI] At least it
would stop the shame...

17
00:01:08,750 --> 00:01:10,750
I sold my wife...

18
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:13,791
I sold my wife to the bandits!

19
00:01:13,875 --> 00:01:15,250
[KIKUCHIYO] Rikichi...

20
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:17,208
[RIKICHI SOBS]

21
00:01:20,333 --> 00:01:25,166
[KIKUCHIYO] So, I don't suppose
those Nobuseri were you guys?!

22
00:01:26,875 --> 00:01:31,833
♪ opening song ♪

23
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,291
[MOSUKE] The samurai
should be here by now.

24
00:03:07,375 --> 00:03:08,625
[GOSAKU]
Rikichi and the Water Priestess

25
00:03:08,708 --> 00:03:11,458
haven't sent us a
letter in a long time.

26
00:03:11,541 --> 00:03:15,083
[MANZO] It was a stupid
idea in the first place.

27
00:03:15,166 --> 00:03:16,875
Now what are
we s'posed to do?

28
00:03:16,958 --> 00:03:19,958
Samurai or not,
the bandits are coming.

29
00:03:21,291 --> 00:03:23,875
[GOSAKU] The only thing
we can do now is wait.

30
00:03:23,958 --> 00:03:25,791
Wait for the bandits
to come for us...

31
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:27,875
Wait for the
samurai to save us...

32
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:31,208
Wait for the sun to shine...
Wait for the rain to fall...

33
00:03:31,291 --> 00:03:35,416
[MOSUKE] We're good at waiting.
That's what farmers do.

34
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,458
[MANZO]
The crop looks good this year.

35
00:03:37,541 --> 00:03:40,458
The rice is bending already.

36
00:03:40,541 --> 00:03:43,125
We won't be able to hold off
the harvest much longer.

37
00:03:43,208 --> 00:03:46,625
[ELDER] We will hold off the
harvest as long as we must.

38
00:03:46,708 --> 00:03:48,875
[MOSUKE] Elder!

39
00:03:48,958 --> 00:03:52,708
We meant no disrespect, but
we can't wait for them forever.

40
00:03:52,791 --> 00:03:55,041
If we harvest it now,
the bandits will come.

41
00:03:55,125 --> 00:03:58,166
Is that what you want?

42
00:03:58,250 --> 00:04:01,541
We wait as long as we must
until the samurai are here.

43
00:04:01,625 --> 00:04:03,791
[YOHEI] But the bandits will
come to check on the crop!

44
00:04:03,875 --> 00:04:06,916
What do we say when
they ask why we're waiting?

45
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,041
[ELDER] We're the ones
that know the rice. Not them.

46
00:04:09,125 --> 00:04:10,875
Remember that!

47
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:15,000
If we say we cannot harvest
the crop yet... then we cannot!

48
00:04:28,541 --> 00:04:33,333
[VILLAGERS YELL]

49
00:05:00,208 --> 00:05:03,666
[VILLAGERS SCREAM]

50
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:27,541
[RIKICHI] Honoka?

51
00:05:27,625 --> 00:05:29,041
You look like
you've seen a ghost.

52
00:05:29,125 --> 00:05:31,875
Maybe we should rest
here for a minute?

53
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:33,833
Honoka, this waterway
leads to the entrance

54
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:35,541
on the other
side, correct?

55
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:38,875
There's really no need
for you to guide us.

56
00:05:38,958 --> 00:05:40,541
Not quite.

57
00:05:41,916 --> 00:05:45,250
The route splits into
different directions up ahead.

58
00:05:45,333 --> 00:05:47,041
You'll need someone
familiar with the path

59
00:05:47,125 --> 00:05:49,708
who can lead
you to the Bandits.

60
00:05:54,166 --> 00:05:55,375
Follow me.

61
00:05:55,458 --> 00:05:58,000
[GOROBEI] Thank you for
your help, Lady Honoka.

62
00:05:58,083 --> 00:06:00,333
Anybody else think
Kikuchiyo's turning out to be

63
00:06:00,416 --> 00:06:02,291
a little more trouble
than he's worth?

64
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:04,958
Starting to feel like we're
cleaning up after a teenager.

65
00:06:05,041 --> 00:06:06,791
More like a toddler.

66
00:06:06,875 --> 00:06:10,000
Ah... But that's part
of his charm, isn't it?

67
00:06:10,083 --> 00:06:12,083
Is that what we're calling it?

68
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:28,958
[KOMACHI] Hey sis?

69
00:06:29,041 --> 00:06:31,583
I think he's asleep now.

70
00:06:31,666 --> 00:06:34,958
I know how badly he
wanted to go with Kambei.

71
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:37,541
Yeah, but if he did, he just
would've been in the way.

72
00:06:37,625 --> 00:06:39,250
Ah... Shh...

73
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:41,000
I think I know
what you meant before.

74
00:06:41,083 --> 00:06:44,708
He doesn't have the scent
of battle like the others do.

75
00:06:44,791 --> 00:06:47,916
Katsushiro just
isn't that scary.

76
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:51,333
[KATSUSHIRO GROANS]

77
00:06:59,875 --> 00:07:02,041
What is it, Great Samurai?

78
00:07:02,125 --> 00:07:03,125
We're surrounded.

79
00:07:03,208 --> 00:07:04,333
[HONOKA AND RIKICHI GASP]

80
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:13,708
[RIKICHI] The bandits.

81
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:16,916
Great...!
A welcoming party!

82
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,416
But why...?
How'd they know?

83
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,458
Gorobei... protect
Lady Honoka and Rikichi.

84
00:07:22,541 --> 00:07:23,500
[GOROBEI] You got it.

85
00:07:23,583 --> 00:07:25,541
But I want to fight, too!

86
00:07:28,125 --> 00:07:30,541
[RAIDEN 1] I see the
rumors were true, then.

87
00:07:30,625 --> 00:07:33,833
[RAIDEN 2] And they reek of the
filthy peasants they're with.

88
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:37,750
What is it you want from us?

89
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:41,583
[RAIDEN 1] You are the samurai
hired by the peasants, correct?

90
00:07:41,666 --> 00:07:43,958
So much for surprises.

91
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,375
And what if we are?

92
00:07:49,458 --> 00:07:52,916
[RAIDEN 1] Then we cannot
allow you to go free.

93
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,500
[KAMBEI]
How you have fallen.

94
00:07:54,583 --> 00:07:55,666
[RAIDEN 1] What?!

95
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:57,583
You've given up
your honor as samurai

96
00:07:57,666 --> 00:08:00,708
and reduced yourselves
to common thieves...

97
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:02,250
Have you no shame?

98
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:05,083
[RAIDEN 1] You allow yourself
to be hired for rice...

99
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:08,541
and you dare talk
to me about shame?!

100
00:08:09,416 --> 00:08:10,750
Great Samurai!

101
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:13,333
[RAIDEN 1] What--?

102
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:23,208
[KAMBEI] I'm amazed you
were ever called samurai.

103
00:08:23,291 --> 00:08:23,958
Shichiroji!

104
00:08:24,041 --> 00:08:25,583
[SHICHIROJI] Right!

105
00:08:36,666 --> 00:08:39,666
You sure know how to
heat things up, old man.

106
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:41,333
[RAIDEN 2] Kill them.

107
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:47,833
Wood Chop Strike!

108
00:08:47,916 --> 00:08:49,208
[ROBOT GUY YELLS]

109
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:52,666
Yeah, that was sloppy.

110
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:54,541
This way! Quickly!

111
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,500
[GOROBEI YELLS]

112
00:09:06,583 --> 00:09:07,875
[GOROBEI MOANS]

113
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:18,500
They're incredible.

114
00:09:26,625 --> 00:09:27,833
[GUNSHOT]

115
00:09:27,916 --> 00:09:29,291
Kambeii-sama!

116
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:38,791
Packs quite a wallop...
I should've tried guns before.

117
00:09:38,875 --> 00:09:41,750
[RAIDEN 2]
Hyogo! What are you doing here?

118
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:45,083
[SHICHIROJI]
Kambei-sama, hold on!

119
00:09:45,166 --> 00:09:47,625
[GUNSHOT]

120
00:09:47,708 --> 00:09:50,750
[HYOGO] Actually, I'd rather
you stayed there for now.

121
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:57,208
[HYOGO GASPS]

122
00:10:07,125 --> 00:10:08,791
[RAIDEN 2]
What the hell?

123
00:10:13,458 --> 00:10:14,625
[RAIDEN 2] You...!

124
00:10:40,208 --> 00:10:43,333
[KYUZO] Only I will have
the pleasure of killing you.

125
00:10:46,333 --> 00:10:47,750
[HYOGO GRUNTS]

126
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:48,833
[GUNSHOT]

127
00:10:53,583 --> 00:10:55,083
[SOBEI] You can stop.

128
00:10:55,166 --> 00:10:56,833
[HYOGO]
Why would I do that?

129
00:10:56,916 --> 00:10:58,916
[SOBEI] We know how
strong they are now.

130
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:02,041
That's all we needed.
We're leaving.

131
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:07,333
So it was a test.

132
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:08,875
You alright?

133
00:11:10,208 --> 00:11:14,250
I am sorry that you can
no longer return to your allies.

134
00:11:18,208 --> 00:11:19,666
[KAMBEI]
Let him go.

135
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:37,958
[SHICHIROJI]
Does it hurt?

136
00:11:38,041 --> 00:11:40,250
No. It's just a scratch.

137
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:45,791
Are you all right?

138
00:11:45,875 --> 00:11:47,333
Yes, we're fine...

139
00:11:47,416 --> 00:11:49,875
The Water Priestess was right
about all of you samurai...

140
00:11:49,958 --> 00:11:51,875
I've never seen anything
like the way you fight!

141
00:11:51,958 --> 00:11:53,000
It's amazing...!

142
00:11:53,083 --> 00:11:54,291
The bandits
threatening our village

143
00:11:54,375 --> 00:11:56,916
don't stand
a chance against you.

144
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,416
We can't withstand firearms.

145
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:00,750
But...

146
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:02,958
During the war I watched
hundreds of fellow samurai

147
00:12:03,041 --> 00:12:06,250
fall to men with
guns and no honor.

148
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:09,375
Heh. You know somehow
I didn't expect Maro's men

149
00:12:09,458 --> 00:12:10,833
to use the bandits against us.

150
00:12:10,916 --> 00:12:12,125
But I guess I underestimated

151
00:12:12,208 --> 00:12:14,875
the buying power of the
merchants, didn't I?

152
00:12:14,958 --> 00:12:16,250
So that's it...

153
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:19,166
I wondered how they were
able to ambush us like that.

154
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:22,250
The Shikimoribito have numerous
exits up to the surface...

155
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:26,166
I wonder how they
knew we'd use this one?

156
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:28,208
[KAMBEI] Why don't you
tell us, Lady Honoka.

157
00:12:28,291 --> 00:12:29,416
[HONOKA AND RIKICHI GASP]

158
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:32,333
You gotta
be kidding me.

159
00:12:32,416 --> 00:12:33,833
What's this about?

160
00:12:33,916 --> 00:12:36,791
She guided us straight to
this exit without hesitation.

161
00:12:36,875 --> 00:12:38,666
Yes... She did.

162
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,708
Have you forgotten that
bandits destroyed her village

163
00:12:40,791 --> 00:12:42,458
and killed her family...?

164
00:12:42,541 --> 00:12:44,291
What reason would she
have for helping them?

165
00:12:44,375 --> 00:12:46,041
Her survival, perhaps?

166
00:12:46,125 --> 00:12:49,083
[RIKICHI]
Not you, too, Gorobei!

167
00:12:49,166 --> 00:12:51,625
[SHIKIMORI 1]
Do not blame her.

168
00:12:51,708 --> 00:12:53,916
[GOROBEI]
The Guardians...

169
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,041
Hey, whaddya know?

170
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:56,416
Turns out
they can talk!

171
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:58,041
Afternoon, gentlemen.

172
00:12:58,125 --> 00:13:00,000
[SHIKIMORI 1]
Your suspicions are justified.

173
00:13:00,083 --> 00:13:02,208
She is a Nobuseri spy.

174
00:13:02,291 --> 00:13:04,791
But your harm was
not her desire.

175
00:13:04,875 --> 00:13:05,875
Oh, sure...

176
00:13:05,958 --> 00:13:07,500
She only ratted us
out to the enemy--

177
00:13:07,583 --> 00:13:10,125
why would we
blame her for that?

178
00:13:36,458 --> 00:13:38,875
[KIKUCHIYO]
Come on! Kill me, already!

179
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:40,875
What, you afraid to
spill a little oil?

180
00:13:40,958 --> 00:13:45,166
Come on, you little soft-handed
weakling chicken bastards!

181
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:47,083
[HYOGO] Silence!

182
00:13:47,166 --> 00:13:49,375
You know, I really
do enjoy this gun...

183
00:13:49,458 --> 00:13:52,083
It has a versatility
that a sword simply lacks.

184
00:13:52,166 --> 00:13:53,875
[KIKUCHIYO]
A samurai with a gun!

185
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:55,458
You're a disgrace!

186
00:13:55,541 --> 00:13:58,666
Heh... Keep it up and you may
just get your wish after all...

187
00:13:58,750 --> 00:14:01,416
The young master did make
a request for your head!

188
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:02,708
[KIKUCHIYO]
Ah, cram it.

189
00:14:02,791 --> 00:14:04,791
[SOBEI]
Your men are incompetent.

190
00:14:04,875 --> 00:14:08,458
We were told there were five
samurai besides this one.

191
00:14:08,541 --> 00:14:09,625
[HYOGO] 
There were.

192
00:14:09,708 --> 00:14:11,291
[SOBEI]
Kyuzo, was it?

193
00:14:11,375 --> 00:14:14,291
I'm surprised Maro would
employ such a traitor.

194
00:14:14,375 --> 00:14:16,416
You should watch what
you say about my Lord--

195
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:17,916
though I'd be curious
to know where you get

196
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,916
such detailed information.

197
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,916
[SOBEI] Ha, ha, ha, ha...
I'm sure you would.

198
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,166
[HYOGO GRUNTS]

199
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:25,708
[KIKUCHIYO LAUGHS]

200
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:28,208
[KIKUCHIYO] Fight! Fight!
Kick him in the gears!

201
00:14:28,291 --> 00:14:30,291
[THUD]

202
00:14:30,375 --> 00:14:31,083
Aww... sorry.

203
00:14:31,166 --> 00:14:32,541
Rest assured, Sobei-dono,

204
00:14:32,625 --> 00:14:34,625
I fully intend to correct
that mistake, but I think

205
00:14:34,708 --> 00:14:37,833
we should stop those peasants
and their samurai first.

206
00:14:37,916 --> 00:14:39,375
[SOBEI] Agreed.

207
00:14:39,458 --> 00:14:40,708
[KIKUCHIYO]
Hey. You guys.

208
00:14:40,791 --> 00:14:42,500
You better finish me off now.

209
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:44,625
Otherwise you're
gonna regret it!

210
00:14:44,708 --> 00:14:47,125
[KIKUCHIYO LAUGHS LOUDLY]

211
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:48,625
[SOBEI] 
Just kill him already.

212
00:14:48,708 --> 00:14:50,416
He's annoying.

213
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:51,500
[HYOGO] Not yet.

214
00:14:51,583 --> 00:14:54,375
He may still be of use to us.

215
00:14:57,750 --> 00:15:00,250
[SHIKIMORI 1] The Nobuseri
who used Honoka as a spy

216
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:02,708
were after our energy
cell generators...

217
00:15:02,791 --> 00:15:05,666
They're trying to gain
control of the technology.

218
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:07,625
But how did
you know all that?

219
00:15:07,708 --> 00:15:09,291
[SHIKIMORI 1]
You underestimate us.

220
00:15:09,375 --> 00:15:11,291
Letting a mole 
relay misinformation

221
00:15:11,375 --> 00:15:14,500
is basic strategy.

222
00:15:14,583 --> 00:15:16,875
[HEIHACHI] So, I take it the
bandits know everything about us

223
00:15:16,958 --> 00:15:18,416
and our mission, right?

224
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,000
Yes.

225
00:15:20,083 --> 00:15:21,375
But why...?

226
00:15:21,458 --> 00:15:23,708
That story about your family
being killed by bandits,

227
00:15:23,791 --> 00:15:25,125
was that all a lie?

228
00:15:25,208 --> 00:15:27,291
No, it was all
true... except...

229
00:15:27,375 --> 00:15:29,041
Except what?

230
00:15:29,125 --> 00:15:31,666
My sister...
My little sis--

231
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:33,166
[HONOKA SOBS]

232
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:36,000
They took her, didn't they?
Just like they took my wife.

233
00:15:36,083 --> 00:15:37,208
[HONOKA]
They promised...

234
00:15:37,291 --> 00:15:39,916
not to hurt my sister
if I obeyed them...

235
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:43,041
so I did everything
they told me to.

236
00:15:43,125 --> 00:15:44,750
[RIKICHI]
You believed them?!

237
00:15:44,833 --> 00:15:46,583
She did what
she had to do.

238
00:15:46,666 --> 00:15:47,875
Not that...

239
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:49,625
She didn't
have to do that.

240
00:15:49,708 --> 00:15:51,916
Isn't that why your wife
let the Bandits take her?

241
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:54,625
To protect the people she loved?

242
00:15:54,708 --> 00:15:58,125
We do what we must,
Rikichi. All of us.

243
00:15:59,791 --> 00:16:01,916
You can't blame her for that.

244
00:16:03,125 --> 00:16:05,458
[HONOKA SOBS]

245
00:16:05,541 --> 00:16:07,458
I, too, searched
for a way to survive,

246
00:16:07,541 --> 00:16:10,291
and found a life as
a street performer.

247
00:16:10,375 --> 00:16:13,208
Compromise is
the age we live in.

248
00:16:13,291 --> 00:16:16,041
Tell us what you told them.

249
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:18,875
I told them you were headed
to Kanna village after this.

250
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:21,250
You told them what?!

251
00:16:21,333 --> 00:16:23,458
[KAMBEI SIGHS]

252
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:27,708
What are you doing?

253
00:16:27,791 --> 00:16:30,666
You're up...!
Are you feeling better already?

254
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:33,208
Yes, and my fever's gone, too.

255
00:16:33,291 --> 00:16:35,625
It's the medicine!
It worked, huh?!

256
00:16:35,708 --> 00:16:36,958
I'm going after them.

257
00:16:37,041 --> 00:16:38,500
[KIRARA] But...

258
00:16:38,583 --> 00:16:40,875
Sensei has finally acknowledged
me as part of the team...

259
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:43,250
A samurai must always
be prepared for battle,

260
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:45,583
so I must do my duty.

261
00:16:50,166 --> 00:16:51,791
Huh...?

262
00:16:52,708 --> 00:16:55,125
So how do you want to do this?

263
00:16:56,166 --> 00:16:58,041
Please don't hurt her,
Great Samurai.

264
00:16:58,125 --> 00:16:59,375
[HEIHACHI]
If we let her live,

265
00:16:59,458 --> 00:17:01,291
she'll endanger
the Guardians, too.

266
00:17:01,375 --> 00:17:03,875
[SHIKIMORI 1]
Do not worry about us, samurai.

267
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,250
[KAMBEI]
Lady Honoka.

268
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:15,000
We will reunite
you and your sister.

269
00:17:17,416 --> 00:17:18,958
[RIKICHI]
Thank you, Great Samurai!

270
00:17:19,041 --> 00:17:21,583
Aren't you being
a little easy on her?

271
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:25,000
It is not a samurai's
duty to punish someone.

272
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:28,625
Shikimoribito.

273
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:29,958
[SHIKIMORI 1] Yes?

274
00:17:30,041 --> 00:17:32,791
May I leave Lady Honoka
and Rikichi in your care?

275
00:17:32,875 --> 00:17:34,458
[SHIKIMORI 1]
Certainly.

276
00:17:36,541 --> 00:17:37,750
[GROUP GASPS]

277
00:17:43,083 --> 00:17:48,250
[GUNSHOTS]

278
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:49,416
[HYOGO] Kyuzo.

279
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:52,000
Now why did you go
and kill that bandit?

280
00:17:52,083 --> 00:17:55,166
The village of Kanna is
defying the laws of this land.

281
00:17:55,250 --> 00:17:58,375
They need to be
taught a lesson.

282
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:02,875
Don't tell me you're
causing all this trouble

283
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:06,000
just to fight a silly old man.

284
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,750
Killing one poor old samurai

285
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:16,125
isn't going to win you
any fame, you know...

286
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:17,166
Tell you what...

287
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:19,375
I'll keep this a
secret from our Lord

288
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:22,458
if you come back with me
to Kougakyo right now.

289
00:18:22,541 --> 00:18:24,625
You know I don't
want to hurt you.

290
00:18:25,625 --> 00:18:26,875
Kyuzo-dono.

291
00:18:26,958 --> 00:18:29,000
He did... all this?

292
00:18:29,083 --> 00:18:32,000
[HEIHACHI] Looks like they're
not the forgiving type.

293
00:18:32,083 --> 00:18:33,625
[KIKUCHIYO]
Ow! Ow! Ow!

294
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:35,041
Kikuchiyo-dono!

295
00:18:35,125 --> 00:18:36,666
[GOROBEI]
Are you sure that's wise?

296
00:18:39,583 --> 00:18:41,416
No.

297
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,750
Kambeii-sama!

298
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:44,000
[GUNSHOT]

299
00:18:44,083 --> 00:18:45,041
Damn it.

300
00:18:45,125 --> 00:18:46,458
[KIKUCHIYO]
Ha ha!

301
00:18:46,541 --> 00:18:49,166
Dirty tricks like using a
hostage don't work on him,

302
00:18:49,250 --> 00:18:50,916
you powder-faced freak!

303
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,375
Shut up.

304
00:18:52,458 --> 00:18:53,875
[KIKUCHIYO]
Didn't you know?

305
00:18:53,958 --> 00:18:54,750
He...

306
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:56,625
No, they...

307
00:18:56,708 --> 00:18:59,333
...are samurai!

308
00:19:01,541 --> 00:19:03,083
And real ones, too.

309
00:19:03,166 --> 00:19:06,125
Not gun-toting,
fancy-dressed fakes like you.

310
00:19:06,208 --> 00:19:07,583
You follow me?

311
00:19:07,666 --> 00:19:10,666
[KIKUCHIYO LAUGHS]

312
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:13,583
Kyuzo...! If you want to
fight against him that badly,

313
00:19:13,666 --> 00:19:15,083
then go ahead and do it!

314
00:19:15,166 --> 00:19:18,375
I'll even watch! You can
have the honor of his death.

315
00:19:18,458 --> 00:19:20,291
If you succeed
and rejoin us today,

316
00:19:20,375 --> 00:19:22,375
your actions will
go unquestioned...

317
00:19:22,458 --> 00:19:25,333
If you die, then
I'll kill him myself.

318
00:19:25,416 --> 00:19:29,125
Regardless of the outcome,
we will have finished our job.

319
00:19:35,166 --> 00:19:37,000
[SHICHIROJI]
Kambei-sama!

320
00:20:02,708 --> 00:20:03,166
Damn it!

321
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:04,458
[GUNSHOT]

322
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:09,666
[KIKUCHIYO GRUNTS]

323
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:11,625
Kyuzo!

324
00:20:25,625 --> 00:20:26,708
[KATSUSHIRO GASPS]

325
00:20:26,791 --> 00:20:29,000
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

326
00:20:31,416 --> 00:20:34,291
[KIKUCHIYO]
Ha, haaaa! That felt good!

327
00:20:34,375 --> 00:20:35,875
Thanks for the help, Katsu!

328
00:20:35,958 --> 00:20:37,750
Katsushiro.
You all right?

329
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:39,625
Yes, Sensei.

330
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:41,166
I'm fine...

331
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:43,291
The Guardians brought me
here so I could help you.

332
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:44,958
[KOMACHI] Hey...!

333
00:20:45,041 --> 00:20:47,041
We wanna help, too, Kambei!

334
00:20:47,125 --> 00:20:49,458
[KIKUCHIYO] Well what are you
gonna do? Bug 'em to death?

335
00:20:49,541 --> 00:20:51,875
[GROUP LAUGHS]

336
00:20:53,291 --> 00:20:56,708
[HYOGO] You've fallen
for our trap, samurai.

337
00:20:56,791 --> 00:20:58,416
Right about now, Sobei-dono

338
00:20:58,500 --> 00:21:00,875
should be arriving
at the Upper Shrine.

339
00:21:00,958 --> 00:21:04,875
Soon all the Nobuseri
will know of your plan.

340
00:21:06,666 --> 00:21:10,958
Why... Kyuzo...? Why did you...

341
00:21:13,166 --> 00:21:16,541
Because... I wanted to live.

342
00:21:17,958 --> 00:21:20,708
You're a hopeless fool.

343
00:21:26,666 --> 00:21:28,541
May I ask you
to come with us?

344
00:21:28,625 --> 00:21:29,916
When do we leave?

345
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,458
Immediately.

346
00:21:34,541 --> 00:21:36,916
[SHIKIMORI 1] We will
be sorry to see you go.

347
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,916
The Nobuseri know
about our mission now,

348
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,041
so I'm afraid we have
no time to spare.

349
00:21:41,125 --> 00:21:42,958
Great Samurai?

350
00:21:43,041 --> 00:21:44,750
[KAMBEI] Don't worry
about what happened.

351
00:21:44,833 --> 00:21:45,916
You wait here.

352
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,083
My little sister
and Rikichi's wife--

353
00:21:48,166 --> 00:21:49,833
the bandits are probably
keeping them both

354
00:21:49,916 --> 00:21:51,833
at the Upper Shrine.

355
00:21:51,916 --> 00:21:53,291
[KAMBEI] Let's go.

356
00:21:56,125 --> 00:21:58,125
That man is our enemy.

357
00:22:09,541 --> 00:22:11,708
[GENZO]
We heard a disturbing rumor...

358
00:22:11,791 --> 00:22:14,291
And we'd like to know
whether or not it's true.

359
00:22:14,375 --> 00:22:15,541
[ELDER] Yes?

360
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:17,291
[GENZO] We heard that
this village was trying

361
00:22:17,375 --> 00:22:20,958
to hire some samurai
to defeat the Nobuseri.

362
00:22:21,041 --> 00:22:22,708
Is that true?

363
00:22:22,791 --> 00:22:24,625
Who told you such
an outrageous tale?

364
00:22:24,708 --> 00:22:25,958
We're peasants.

365
00:22:26,041 --> 00:22:28,250
We couldn't afford to hire
samurai if we wanted to.

366
00:22:28,333 --> 00:22:30,958
You know it doesn't do
any good to lie to us.

367
00:22:31,041 --> 00:22:33,250
[ELDER]
I never lie.

368
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:35,125
[GENZO]
We could burn the village now,

369
00:22:35,208 --> 00:22:36,500
and be done with it...

370
00:22:36,583 --> 00:22:39,625
However, our leader has
given you a grace period...

371
00:22:39,708 --> 00:22:42,458
Be thankful for his generosity.

372
00:22:42,541 --> 00:22:44,458
If it's true we'll find out...

373
00:22:44,541 --> 00:22:47,250
And each one of you
will be punished.

374
00:22:48,583 --> 00:22:51,833
If any samurai come here,
you will hand them over to us,

375
00:22:51,916 --> 00:22:55,458
and we will forget
about this troubling rumor.

376
00:22:55,541 --> 00:22:57,166
Think of the
well-being of the village

377
00:22:57,250 --> 00:23:00,375
and I'm sure you'll
know what to do.

378
00:23:00,458 --> 00:23:02,041
[ELDER SIGHS]

379
00:23:04,083 --> 00:23:06,666
All of you need to
stop looking up in hope...

380
00:23:06,750 --> 00:23:09,833
Just keep your eyes down
on the dirt where they belong.

381
00:23:09,916 --> 00:23:11,791
[GENZO LAUGHS]

382
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:18,458
♪ closing song ♪

383
00:25:23,916 --> 00:25:26,500
[KOMACHI] Dear Okara,
I've got exciting news today!

384
00:25:26,583 --> 00:25:28,625
We found samurai number six!

385
00:25:28,708 --> 00:25:30,166
Remember Kyuzo?

386
00:25:30,250 --> 00:25:32,291
That weird one I told you about
who's scary 'cause he hardly

387
00:25:32,375 --> 00:25:34,833
ever says anything, and he's
strong and uses two swords

388
00:25:34,916 --> 00:25:36,333
and he tried to kill Kambei?

389
00:25:36,416 --> 00:25:39,833
Well now he's on our side!
Yeah, isn't that crazy?

390
00:25:39,916 --> 00:25:41,208
He's really good at fighting,

391
00:25:41,291 --> 00:25:43,041
but I don't think
I like him, personally.

392
00:25:43,125 --> 00:25:45,000
You just can't trust
the quiet ones.

393
00:25:45,083 --> 00:25:46,583
Besides, sis doesn't
like him either,

394
00:25:46,666 --> 00:25:48,791
and it makes me nervous
seeing her upset.

395
00:25:48,875 --> 00:25:51,291
Oh, and another thing--if he
was going to join us all along,

396
00:25:51,375 --> 00:25:53,375
why didn't he just say
so back in the city,

397
00:25:53,458 --> 00:25:55,208
and save us all this time?

398
00:25:55,291 --> 00:25:57,583
Honestly, sometimes
the way these samurai act

399
00:25:57,666 --> 00:25:59,416
doesn't make any sense...

400
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:00,583
Oh yeah, more news!

401
00:26:00,666 --> 00:26:02,125
Katsushiro's feeling better.

402
00:26:02,208 --> 00:26:04,916
The medicine those Guardians
gave him really did the trick.

403
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,250
They should sell that stuff--

404
00:26:06,333 --> 00:26:08,333
they'd probably get even
richer than the merchants!

405
00:26:08,416 --> 00:26:11,208
Then maybe they could buy
clothes that weren't so creepy.

406
00:26:11,291 --> 00:26:13,333
But anyway, tell our Elder
we're crossing the desert,

407
00:26:13,416 --> 00:26:15,083
and we should get
back to Kanna soon!

408
00:26:15,166 --> 00:26:18,416
Can't wait to introduce
you to Kiku! Bye-bye!

